                {
                    "id": "photon_energy_visible_band_sweep",
                    "description": "Sweep λ across the visible band 380-780 nm (the canonical human-visible-light range, equivalently the PAR-band-extended range) at fine resolution, surfacing the per-photon energy variation across the visible spectrum. At λ=380 nm (violet), Δε ≈ 5.23e-19 J ≈ 3.27 eV; at λ=500 nm (yellow-green, default), Δε ≈ 3.97e-19 J ≈ 2.48 eV; at λ=650 nm (red), Δε ≈ 3.06e-19 J ≈ 1.91 eV; at λ=780 nm (deep-red / near-IR boundary), Δε ≈ 2.55e-19 J ≈ 1.59 eV. The factor-of-2 variation across the visible band drives the wavelength-dependence of photochemical quantum yields in chlorophyll-a, retinal opsins, and other visible-active photoreceptor pigments. Anchors the visible-band radiative-transfer application where per-photon energy enters the quantum-yield calculation (photons absorbed per unit energy = energy absorbed / Δε).",
